# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The target structure consists of 9 building blocks arranged in 3 layers:
- Bottom layer: 3 red blocks (a double-arch block, a curved slide block, and a single arch block)
- Middle layer: 3 blocks (a blue cube, a green horizontal rectangular block, and a red single arch block)
- Top layer: 3 blocks (a red single arch block with an orange triangular roof piece on top, and a green horizontal rectangular block)

## Spatial Relationships
- Bottom layer: A red double-arch block (left side) connects to a red curved slide block (middle), which connects to a red single arch block (right side)
- Middle layer: A blue cube sits on the right end of the bottom layer, with a green horizontal block spanning across the top of the red arch. A red single arch block sits on the far left.
- Top layer: A red single arch block sits on top of the green block on the right side, topped with an orange triangular roof piece. Another green horizontal block spans from the left red arch.

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the analysis, I need the following blocks:
- Block 1: Red single arch (×4)

- Block 3: Red double-arch (×1)
- Block 5: Blue cube (×1)
- Block 10: Green horizontal rectangular block (×2)
- Block 16: Orange triangular roof (×1)
